1
00:00:01,335 --> 00:00:04,213
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:24,710 --> 00:01:27,129
[Near] The current Kira is foolish
and overconfident,

3
00:01:27,212 --> 00:01:29,756
not to mention unusually cooperative
with the Task Force.

4
00:01:30,215 --> 00:01:32,968
In fact, I suspect he's working
hand in hand with them.

5
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:35,721
-You think so?
-That would make the second L and Kira...

6
00:01:36,263 --> 00:01:37,764
one and the same person.

7
00:01:37,973 --> 00:01:39,329
-[monitor beeping]
-[Near] To the members

8
00:01:39,429 --> 00:01:40,809
of the Japanese Task Force...

9
00:01:41,018 --> 00:01:43,186
Was there ever a point
in the investigation

10
00:01:43,312 --> 00:01:45,188
where the second L
was suspected to be Kira,

11
00:01:45,314 --> 00:01:47,274
even if the suspicion was later dropped?

12
00:01:47,357 --> 00:01:50,193
[Light] Near... I have to kill him!

13
00:01:50,485 --> 00:01:54,531
[panting] This is really bad!
Turn on the TV! It's Demegawa.

14
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:58,368
This is Demegawa, live.
My comrades and I have finally pinpointed

15
00:01:58,452 --> 00:02:01,121
the hideout of the evil organization
bent on trying to catch

16
00:02:01,204 --> 00:02:02,706
-our beloved god, Kira.
-[mob yelling]

17
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:04,875
We now have the building
completely surrounded!

18
00:02:04,958 --> 00:02:07,878
TRANSFER

19
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:13,884
[tires screeching]

20
00:02:24,353 --> 00:02:25,562
[jingle playing on TV]

21
00:02:25,646 --> 00:02:27,397
[Demegawa] Fellow Kira supporters,

22
00:02:27,481 --> 00:02:30,317
I urge you, do not rush the building
all at once.

23
00:02:30,942 --> 00:02:34,780
The traitors may attempt to blend in
with the crowd to escape.

24
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:39,743
I am Kira's loyal servant and spokesman.
You must listen to me!

25
00:02:40,118 --> 00:02:44,456
Find them, move them from the building,
and bring them in front of the cameras!

26
00:02:44,665 --> 00:02:47,584
-They'll be a sacrifice to Kira!
-[glass cracking]

27
00:02:47,876 --> 00:02:50,003
[mob yelling]

28
00:02:54,049 --> 00:02:56,134
You can't hide from me. I'll find you.

29
00:02:58,470 --> 00:03:01,473
Near, you've got no choice.
You better evacuate.

30
00:03:02,099 --> 00:03:04,393
You've got some nerve to say that,
being Kira.

31
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:07,229
What? Are you still going on
about that nonsense?

32
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:10,524
Think about it.
With all the anti-Kira groups around,

33
00:03:10,607 --> 00:03:14,111
why is it we're being targeted,
and right after I start suspecting you?

34
00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:16,321
Pretty convenient, if you ask me.

35
00:03:17,114 --> 00:03:19,032
[Light] Near, with all due respect,
you're wrong.

36
00:03:19,116 --> 00:03:20,742
You're jumping to conclusions.

37
00:03:21,368 --> 00:03:23,704
[Near] Members of the Task Force,
please listen to me.

38
00:03:24,162 --> 00:03:27,916
Kira is likely amongst you.
Even as we speak, he is in that room.

39
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:30,502
I'm simply asking you
to think about this carefully.

40
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:31,461
[Aizawa sighs]

41
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:36,299
[Aizawa] "Light is Kira."
This is all sounding way too familiar.

42
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:40,137
The original L also thought
that Light had to be Kira.

43
00:03:46,143 --> 00:03:48,103
[mob yelling]

44
00:03:48,270 --> 00:03:51,523
The first wave of 20 people
will break the door and get inside!

45
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:53,525
-Second wave, stand by!
-[man grunting]

46
00:03:54,818 --> 00:03:56,695
Out of the way, idiot!
We're the first wave!

47
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:58,822
What? Like hell! We're going first!

48
00:04:02,159 --> 00:04:04,911
-Near, we have to evacuate immediately.
-[glass shattering]

49
00:04:04,995 --> 00:04:07,622
[Near] Really, what pathetic people.

50
00:04:07,956 --> 00:04:10,041
I'm not surprised
that there are ordinary people

51
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:11,877
who support what Kira's trying to do.

52
00:04:12,335 --> 00:04:14,796
I'm talking about honest citizens,
who believe in their hearts

53
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:16,590
that by punishing evil doers,

54
00:04:16,673 --> 00:04:19,551
Kira will actually make this world
a better place to live.

55
00:04:19,801 --> 00:04:23,263
But as for this crowd outside,
they're a completely different breed.

56
00:04:23,346 --> 00:04:25,140
They are truly despicable and stupid.

57
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:28,769
This is just a diversion for them.
They're all selfish.

58
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:33,148
I-- I know that, but it still leaves us
with the immediate problem.

59
00:04:33,231 --> 00:04:36,651
[Near] We'll use L's legacy
and the anti-Kira protestors we hired.

60
00:04:37,903 --> 00:04:40,155
Yes, but we only have one shot
with that plan.

61
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:43,992
I'm aware of that, but I can't imagine
a better time to do it.

62
00:04:44,117 --> 00:04:46,036
Besides, it should be interesting.

63
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:53,919
[mob yelling]

64
00:05:02,969 --> 00:05:04,387
Huh? It's...

65
00:05:05,514 --> 00:05:10,477
-It's money!
-[mob yelling and laughing]

66
00:05:15,232 --> 00:05:17,859
Money? It's so much!

67
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:22,781
[Matsuda] What? Whoa.
That's a lot. Amazing!

68
00:05:23,114 --> 00:05:25,450
Man, I wish I were over there right now.

69
00:05:25,534 --> 00:05:26,409
Matsuda!

70
00:05:26,493 --> 00:05:29,454
[laughs] Humans are so interesting.

71
00:05:29,579 --> 00:05:33,500
Of course you can use money to get apples,
so I can kind of understand.

72
00:05:33,583 --> 00:05:36,753
-[man 1] I grabbed it first, you bastard!
-[man 2] Out of the way!

73
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:40,340
[Light] Damn it! He's planning to use
all this chaos to escape into the crowd.

74
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:43,510
Even so, he can't escape
from Demegawa's cameras.

75
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:51,059
Over there, pilot! Go to the floor
where all the money's coming from!

76
00:05:51,643 --> 00:05:54,062
Jeez! What are you doing, Demegawa?

77
00:05:54,145 --> 00:05:56,523
Don't you know that you can't
buy love and peace with money?

78
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:58,275
[Light snarls]

79
00:05:58,859 --> 00:06:02,320
A literal downpour of money
is causing mayhem in Lower Manhattan.

80
00:06:02,821 --> 00:06:05,612
-[reporter] The police have arrived.
-[Light gasps] The police?

81
00:06:05,712 --> 00:06:07,262
[reporter]
They're a welcome sight in the midst

82
00:06:07,337 --> 00:06:09,119
of what can only be called
a full-scale riot.

83
00:06:09,202 --> 00:06:11,246
[Light] This is bad. At this rate...

84
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:16,251
[Near] Let's go.

85
00:06:16,751 --> 00:06:19,963
This is our window of opportunity.
We can leave via the front exit.

86
00:06:20,338 --> 00:06:23,675
It makes sense that the police would have
to mobilize for a riot like this.

87
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:26,845
[Light] Damn! Near was prepared
for this situation.

88
00:06:27,012 --> 00:06:28,930
He's planning to come out
along with the rest of them,

89
00:06:29,014 --> 00:06:31,600
and if I tell Aizawa and the others
to keep an eye on the police,

90
00:06:31,683 --> 00:06:33,894
it'll only make me look
that much more suspicious.

91
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:37,606
[reporter] The police are coming out
of the building. They've secured the area.

92
00:06:40,191 --> 00:06:43,570
[Light] Where is he?
He's gotta be in there somewhere!

93
00:06:44,279 --> 00:06:45,238
But where?

94
00:06:46,907 --> 00:06:47,908
[gasps]

95
00:06:54,789 --> 00:06:55,916
Damn it.

96
00:07:01,963 --> 00:07:03,632
[sirens wailing]

97
00:07:03,882 --> 00:07:07,218
[indistinct police radio chatter]

98
00:07:19,773 --> 00:07:22,233
[groans] How much money
do you think was there?

99
00:07:22,484 --> 00:07:24,975
-Bet it was a lot.
-[Ide] Matsuda, knock it off!

100
00:07:25,075 --> 00:07:27,150
[Matsuda] I bet it was around ten million
dollars or something.

101
00:07:27,275 --> 00:07:29,157
[Ryuk] Ooh, what's that in apples?

102
00:07:33,411 --> 00:07:34,579
-[monitor beeping]
-[gasps]

103
00:07:37,207 --> 00:07:39,501
-Near!
-Already?

104
00:07:42,837 --> 00:07:44,923
-[Near] This is Near.
-[groans]

105
00:07:46,466 --> 00:07:48,468
We've reestablished a secure connection,

106
00:07:48,551 --> 00:07:50,637
so I thought I should give you a call
to let you know.

107
00:07:50,929 --> 00:07:52,931
[Light] You're safe. That's a relief.

108
00:07:53,556 --> 00:07:55,308
To all of you on the Task Force...

109
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:58,269
I'm sure that by now, some of you
are starting to suspect

110
00:07:58,353 --> 00:07:59,646
that Kira may be one of you.

111
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,191
Given the timing of today's attack
on our headquarters,

112
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:05,902
I don't think anyone could blame you
for having doubts.

113
00:08:06,236 --> 00:08:09,239
If you don't suspect the second L
of being Kira by now,

114
00:08:09,364 --> 00:08:10,949
you're in the wrong line of work.

115
00:08:12,450 --> 00:08:15,203
The number I gave you
the day before has been reconnected.

116
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:17,372
Please feel free to call anytime you like.

117
00:08:18,415 --> 00:08:21,960
-Well then, I'll be waiting for your call.
-[Aizawa sighs]

118
00:08:22,127 --> 00:08:23,003
[chuckles]

119
00:08:26,548 --> 00:08:30,135
Those were some strong words.
This guy's pretty sure of himself.

120
00:08:33,138 --> 00:08:37,809
I've been thinking, and if any of you want
to cooperate with Near, please go ahead.

121
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:41,688
I'm not particularly satisfied
with the way things are going either.

122
00:08:41,855 --> 00:08:46,526
Ideally, we should cooperate with the SPK.
Maybe this will clear the air a little.

123
00:08:47,235 --> 00:08:49,988
[Matsuda] Still, it kind of feels
like Near's against us, doesn't it?

124
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:16,139
[Aizawa sighs] When I think
about Deputy Director Yagami,

125
00:09:16,306 --> 00:09:20,727
I don't wanna suspect Light,
even a little bit, butâ€¦ [sighs]

126
00:09:21,061 --> 00:09:22,729
-[Yumi] Dad?
-Huh?

127
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:26,232
Welcome back. I didn't know
you were gonna be home tonight.

128
00:09:26,441 --> 00:09:28,777
Oh, yeah. What are you still doing awake?

129
00:09:29,069 --> 00:09:30,862
I've got a couple of exams coming up.

130
00:09:31,071 --> 00:09:34,449
I see. Well, don't push yourself
too hard, okay?

131
00:09:34,532 --> 00:09:37,077
-'Kay. You too, Dad.
-[chuckles]

132
00:09:41,831 --> 00:09:42,999
Hmm...

133
00:09:49,714 --> 00:09:50,924
[ice cubes clinking]

134
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:59,474
[Light] I wouldn't be surprised
if one of the others contacted Near.

135
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:02,936
It's inevitable.
The problem is what comes after that.

136
00:10:03,394 --> 00:10:05,897
If I'm too late to act,
something might happen

137
00:10:06,022 --> 00:10:07,774
that I won't be able to take back.

138
00:10:11,986 --> 00:10:13,780
I've got no choice but to do it.

139
00:10:15,198 --> 00:10:16,282
[beeping]

140
00:10:16,741 --> 00:10:19,577
[squeals] An emergency order
from Light! Yay!

141
00:10:20,245 --> 00:10:21,538
[chuckles]

142
00:10:22,539 --> 00:10:24,749
Hmm, file number three.

143
00:10:26,084 --> 00:10:28,753
Huh? [gasps]

144
00:10:31,214 --> 00:10:32,382
No way...

145
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:34,342
[phone ringing]

146
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:38,304
[Near] Yes, this is Near.

147
00:10:38,972 --> 00:10:42,559
[Aizawa] I'm with the Japanese Task Force.
My name is Aizawa.

148
00:11:02,036 --> 00:11:03,163
[bird chirping]

149
00:11:03,413 --> 00:11:05,623
[Misa] So, the time has finally come.

150
00:11:06,124 --> 00:11:11,212
If I do this, my safety is guaranteed,
and I can finally just be a normal wife.

151
00:11:11,421 --> 00:11:12,922
This is what Light wants for me!

152
00:11:13,047 --> 00:11:16,301
He wants me to be happy,
just as a woman should be.

153
00:11:16,593 --> 00:11:19,053
Thank you, Light.

154
00:11:21,848 --> 00:11:24,100
[Near] I see. That's very interesting.

155
00:11:24,184 --> 00:11:26,811
You're saying there were two suspects
in the Kira investigation

156
00:11:26,936 --> 00:11:29,439
that the previous L detained
for more than 50 days,

157
00:11:29,606 --> 00:11:32,734
and they were cleared
based on the 13-day rule, correct?

158
00:11:33,526 --> 00:11:36,863
[Aizawa] Yes, but of course,
that alone doesn't prove they were Kira.

159
00:11:36,988 --> 00:11:39,240
[Near] And L was willing to release them
because of that?

160
00:11:39,365 --> 00:11:41,743
[Aizawa] No. L had Deputy Director Yagami,

161
00:11:41,826 --> 00:11:44,204
the chief detective at the time,
put on an act.

162
00:11:44,704 --> 00:11:47,832
He was instructed to tell the suspects
that they had both been found guilty

163
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:51,920
of being Kira and the second Kira,
and that they were going to be executed.

164
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:54,589
Then, on the way,
the Deputy Director pulled over

165
00:11:54,714 --> 00:11:56,507
and pointed a gun at the suspects.

166
00:11:56,591 --> 00:11:59,427
He said that he would first kill Kira,
then himself.

167
00:12:00,303 --> 00:12:01,304
[Near] Huh.

168
00:12:01,763 --> 00:12:04,182
[Aizawa] The idea was
that if he were Kira,

169
00:12:04,265 --> 00:12:07,143
the suspect would've killed the chief
right then and there.

170
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:10,855
[Near] Kira is quite impressive.

171
00:12:11,105 --> 00:12:14,400
He must have used his detainment
to demonstrate his innocence.

172
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:15,777
Well done.

173
00:12:16,361 --> 00:12:19,656
Out of curiosity, did the suspect
volunteer to be detained

174
00:12:19,739 --> 00:12:22,200
-as part of the investigation?
-Hmm...

175
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:26,496
Come to think of it,
Light did volunteer to be imprisoned.

176
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:31,542
[Near] If he did, then I'd say
that settles the matter, wouldn't you?

177
00:12:32,377 --> 00:12:35,546
So, who was it?
Who were those two suspects?

178
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:38,174
Hmm. I can't tell you that much.

179
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:40,218
I'm willing to cooperate,
but I'm still a member

180
00:12:40,343 --> 00:12:42,387
of the Japanese Task Force,
working under L.

181
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:44,847
[Near] I understand.

182
00:12:45,139 --> 00:12:48,226
Thank you very much.
Your information's been quite valuable.

183
00:12:48,434 --> 00:12:50,645
Especially the part about Shinigami's eyes

184
00:12:50,728 --> 00:12:52,647
that enable you to see
other people's names.

185
00:12:53,064 --> 00:12:55,233
-It was very helpful. Goodbye.
-[hangs up]

186
00:12:57,026 --> 00:12:58,027
[sighs]

187
00:13:02,682 --> 00:13:03,975
[Rester] Will that be enough, Near?

188
00:13:04,081 --> 00:13:05,952
Shouldn't you have pressed
for a little more information?

189
00:13:06,369 --> 00:13:10,081
I think that all things considered,
his level of cooperation is fine for now.

190
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:14,377
And besides, I discovered something
very important.

191
00:13:15,086 --> 00:13:18,881
The person suspected of being Kira
is Deputy Director Yagami's son.

192
00:13:19,007 --> 00:13:20,341
Hmm?

193
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:22,260
[Near] It's the only possible explanation.

194
00:13:22,343 --> 00:13:26,347
Why else would the Deputy Director say
he would kill Kira and then himself?

195
00:13:27,932 --> 00:13:31,811
Therefore, that means the second L,
and the person I think is Kira

196
00:13:31,894 --> 00:13:33,354
can only be one man...

197
00:13:34,439 --> 00:13:35,857
Light Yagami.

198
00:13:45,408 --> 00:13:47,660
-[Aizawa] Light.
-Yes?

199
00:13:48,244 --> 00:13:51,748
There's something you should know.
I phoned Near and talked to him.

200
00:13:51,914 --> 00:13:53,166
[Matsuda gasps]

201
00:13:57,170 --> 00:13:58,504
[Light] Don't worry about it.

202
00:13:58,713 --> 00:14:01,090
After all, I was the one
who recommended it.

203
00:14:01,382 --> 00:14:03,593
So, what did the two of you
end up discussing?

204
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:07,013
[stammers] No, on second thought,
I probably shouldn't ask.

205
00:14:07,096 --> 00:14:10,600
I guess it's not appropriate for me to ask
those kinds of questions if I'm a suspect.

206
00:14:11,476 --> 00:14:12,602
[Aizawa] Hmm...

207
00:14:13,311 --> 00:14:16,314
Don't get me wrong.
I wanna believe that you aren't Kira.

208
00:14:16,439 --> 00:14:19,275
But I've gotta be certain.
I'm sorry to have to do this again,

209
00:14:19,359 --> 00:14:22,278
but I wanna put you under surveillance
until we catch Kira.

210
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:25,281
I'm afraid that goes for Misa Amane
as well.

211
00:14:25,448 --> 00:14:27,325
I'm gonna search your place right now.

212
00:14:27,617 --> 00:14:30,495
There's a possibility that Amane
might have a notebook.

213
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:32,413
[Matsuda] Hang on a second, Aizawa!

214
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:34,916
[Light] No, go right ahead.
Look at it this way,

215
00:14:34,999 --> 00:14:37,919
at least you can prove to everyone
that I'm not sneaking around

216
00:14:38,044 --> 00:14:39,837
and contacting Misa in private, right?

217
00:14:45,093 --> 00:14:47,428
-[keyboard clicking]
-[Matsuda grunts]

218
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:50,014
[door closes]

219
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:55,228
Huh? Mogi?

220
00:14:55,686 --> 00:14:58,231
I'm coming with you.
I wanna make sure too.

221
00:15:01,192 --> 00:15:02,110
[Aizawa] Hmm...

222
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:05,863
It would be best for everyone
if Light wasn't Kira,

223
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:10,993
but if Amane has any evidence on her
that connects her with Kira, then...

224
00:15:15,540 --> 00:15:16,541
[Aizawa sighs]

225
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:20,920
[doorbell rings]

226
00:15:38,479 --> 00:15:39,355
[both gasp]

227
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,232
[Misa] Mochi! Monchichi!

228
00:15:41,607 --> 00:15:44,068
Long time no see, you two!

229
00:15:44,402 --> 00:15:48,239
Light hasn't been home at all lately,
so I've been super bored.

230
00:15:48,573 --> 00:15:51,617
[Aizawa groans] Well, there's no way
she's got the notebook hidden

231
00:15:51,701 --> 00:15:52,869
on her dressed like that.

232
00:15:53,244 --> 00:15:55,872
We're just investigating a tip
that there were explosives

233
00:15:55,997 --> 00:15:57,957
planted in L's house.
We think it's a prank,

234
00:15:58,040 --> 00:15:59,959
but we'd like to check the rooms
just in case.

235
00:16:00,042 --> 00:16:03,337
[Misa gasps] What? How about Light?
Is he okay? I have to call him.

236
00:16:03,421 --> 00:16:04,714
No. You can't call him right now.

237
00:16:04,839 --> 00:16:06,048
How come?

238
00:16:06,299 --> 00:16:09,093
[Aizawa] Don't worry. Light's safe
but he's really busy right now.

239
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:12,305
He has some other things he has to do
so he's handed the investigation

240
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:13,598
over to us for the time being.

241
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:18,269
Oh, I get it. Light loves me like crazy,
so he doesn't want me to call him

242
00:16:18,394 --> 00:16:20,104
'cause that'll only make him worry
about me.

243
00:16:21,063 --> 00:16:24,108
[Light] Search as much
as you like, Aizawa.

244
00:16:24,859 --> 00:16:26,903
You won't find the notebook.

245
00:16:31,407 --> 00:16:32,700
[Misa yawns]

246
00:16:36,412 --> 00:16:40,458
Mm, I wouldn't like all this suspicion
to ruin the atmosphere around here.

247
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:42,460
This isn't a social club.

248
00:16:42,543 --> 00:16:45,171
I think Aizawa and Mogi should do
as they see fit.

249
00:16:45,296 --> 00:16:46,380
Hmm. [sighs]

250
00:16:47,632 --> 00:16:49,008
It's time for Kira's Kingdom.

251
00:16:51,552 --> 00:16:53,471
[jingle playing on TV]

252
00:16:53,554 --> 00:16:55,848
KIRA'S KINGDOM

253
00:16:57,016 --> 00:17:00,061
[Demegawa] Greetings to all
my fellow Kira worshippers.

254
00:17:00,144 --> 00:17:03,439
I am Demegawa, the voice of our god, Kira.

255
00:17:03,523 --> 00:17:08,861
Behold! This is the new Kira's Kingdom,
which shares its name with this program.

256
00:17:09,111 --> 00:17:12,657
Its construction is going smoothly
but will depend on the generous support...

257
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:13,783
ARCHITECT'S CONCEPT

258
00:17:13,866 --> 00:17:15,868
...of our loyal viewers.
Once it has been completed,

259
00:17:15,952 --> 00:17:18,602
let us welcome our god here!

260
00:17:19,163 --> 00:17:21,165
Whoa, talk about bad taste.

261
00:17:21,666 --> 00:17:22,583
[sighs]

262
00:17:26,754 --> 00:17:29,131
[grunts] Hey, so is everything okay?

263
00:17:29,507 --> 00:17:31,676
Oh, yeah. Seems like it was just a prank.

264
00:17:31,884 --> 00:17:33,427
-Oh.
-But just in case,

265
00:17:33,511 --> 00:17:36,430
one of us is gonna stay and keep watch
over you for the next few days.

266
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:38,349
Really? Oh, that would be great.

267
00:17:38,558 --> 00:17:41,102
Mogi, why don't you go back
to headquarters?

268
00:17:41,227 --> 00:17:42,436
I'll stay on guard here.

269
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:44,939
Huh? I'm with Monchichi instead of Mochi?

270
00:17:45,398 --> 00:17:47,775
Hmm? What's wrong? Don't you trust me?

271
00:17:48,150 --> 00:17:51,112
No, you're just not Monchichi
without your old haircut.

272
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:52,446
You're not cute anymore.

273
00:17:52,572 --> 00:17:54,615
-[Mogi chuckles]
-[Aizawa grumbles] Mogi!

274
00:17:54,782 --> 00:17:56,242
Yes, sir, my apologies.

275
00:17:56,409 --> 00:17:57,994
All right, you stay.

276
00:17:58,202 --> 00:17:59,370
[rock music playing]

277
00:17:59,495 --> 00:18:03,124
We are now accepting donations,
starting at the million Yen mark

278
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:06,586
towards the completion of Kira's Kingdom!
So, if you truly support Kira...

279
00:18:06,669 --> 00:18:08,254
[Matsuda] This sounds like a con.

280
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:11,048
[Ide] Yep. Just another scam
at this point.

281
00:18:11,882 --> 00:18:14,218
It doesn't even seem like Kira's style.

282
00:18:14,844 --> 00:18:18,055
[Light] Demegawa...
He's just acting on his own now.

283
00:18:18,598 --> 00:18:21,517
If he keeps doing this, he'll end up
pushing people away from Kira.

284
00:18:21,934 --> 00:18:26,063
I don't need him anymore.
But I can't do much at the moment.

285
00:18:31,402 --> 00:18:33,195
[Matsuda] Hey, welcome back, Aizawa.

286
00:18:35,531 --> 00:18:38,409
[Aizawa] We didn't find a notebook
in Light or Misa's room.

287
00:18:38,909 --> 00:18:40,786
-But still...
-[Light] I understand.

288
00:18:40,953 --> 00:18:44,457
You're more than welcome to keep watch
over Misa and I until you're satisfied.

289
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:46,792
[Demegawa] Next on the program,

290
00:18:47,209 --> 00:18:49,962
it's time for me to introduce
the new leaders I have chosen

291
00:18:50,046 --> 00:18:51,047
for Kira's Kingdom!

292
00:18:55,593 --> 00:18:57,011
The first gentleman is...

293
00:18:57,219 --> 00:18:58,095
[Mikami] Delete.

294
00:18:58,179 --> 00:19:01,182
[splutters and groans]

295
00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:04,810
[all gasp]

296
00:19:04,977 --> 00:19:08,606
[stammering] We will unite with Kira
and work with him!

297
00:19:09,523 --> 00:19:10,650
[Mikami] Delete.

298
00:19:10,941 --> 00:19:11,901
[man groaning]

299
00:19:14,153 --> 00:19:15,946
-[Mikami] Delete!
-[man yells]

300
00:19:16,572 --> 00:19:18,157
[Mikami] Delete!

301
00:19:21,077 --> 00:19:24,789
[Demegawa panting]

302
00:19:28,292 --> 00:19:30,961
[gasps] Save me!

303
00:19:39,679 --> 00:19:41,180
And delete.

304
00:19:41,972 --> 00:19:44,475
-[heart pumping]
-[Demegawa yells]

305
00:19:47,895 --> 00:19:49,689
SAKURA TV
PLEASE STAND BY

306
00:19:52,441 --> 00:19:54,902
[Aizawa gasps] What the hell is this?

307
00:19:55,236 --> 00:19:57,321
Why would Kira kill his own supporters?

308
00:19:57,488 --> 00:19:59,852
[Matsuda] Do you think it's because
they're going overboard with this?

309
00:20:00,574 --> 00:20:04,328
That might be a possibility.
But this is horrible.

310
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:06,122
[Aizawa] What's going on?

311
00:20:06,247 --> 00:20:08,582
There was no chance
for either Misa Amane or Light

312
00:20:08,666 --> 00:20:10,751
to use the notebook to kill Demegawa.

313
00:20:12,461 --> 00:20:14,837
[Light] Mikami...
I can definitely use him!

314
00:20:15,323 --> 00:20:17,659
It seems I was right
to choose him for this.

315
00:20:18,318 --> 00:20:21,237
He understands Kira's beliefs
and ideals perfectly.

316
00:20:21,424 --> 00:20:24,336
And he knows what Kira wants
and doesn't want.

317
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:28,075
Thanks to that, he takes action
without needing my orders.

318
00:20:28,475 --> 00:20:30,800
I had Misa relinquish ownership
of the Death Note.

319
00:20:31,402 --> 00:20:34,241
Before she lost all her memories
of the notebook,

320
00:20:34,483 --> 00:20:38,028
she sent it to someone else,
along with some special instructions.

321
00:20:38,237 --> 00:20:41,240
Now she won't be able to answer
any questions about it.

322
00:20:41,615 --> 00:20:43,367
She's just an ordinary woman.

323
00:20:43,909 --> 00:20:46,579
The main problem was selecting
the next owner.

324
00:20:46,728 --> 00:20:50,062
I saw him trying to speak to Kira
through the television broadcasts.

325
00:20:50,374 --> 00:20:51,513
It was clear he worshipped Kira...

326
00:20:51,568 --> 00:20:52,690
KIRA'S KINGDOM VIEWER SURVEY

327
00:20:52,790 --> 00:20:54,370
DO YOU WANT TO PARTICIPATE
IN THE NEXT SHOW? YES

328
00:20:54,490 --> 00:20:56,629
...from the bottom of his heart.
He would understand that he was chosen

329
00:20:56,764 --> 00:20:58,330
simply by receiving
and accepting the notebook.

330
00:20:58,489 --> 00:20:59,864
SEX: MALE
BIRTHDATE: JUNE 7, 1982, AGE: 27

331
00:21:00,885 --> 00:21:02,219
OCCUPATION: PROSECUTOR

332
00:21:02,511 --> 00:21:05,181
There was no mistake in my selection.

333
00:21:05,431 --> 00:21:07,975
NAME: TERU MIKAMI, YEAR OF BIRTH: 1982
RESIDENCE: KYOTO PREFECTURE

334
00:21:08,184 --> 00:21:12,271
Teru Mikami, he's more than worthy
of becoming the hand of Kira.

335
00:21:13,022 --> 00:21:15,483
[Mikami] Shinigami, thank you
for coming to me.

336
00:21:15,733 --> 00:21:18,736
Now, I'll be able to punish evildoers
with death.

337
00:21:19,195 --> 00:21:21,947
WHAT IS KIRA TO YOU?

338
00:21:23,157 --> 00:21:26,410
[Mikami chuckles] God.

339
00:21:26,827 --> 00:21:33,751
TO BE CONTINUED

340
00:21:36,045 --> 00:21:39,048
[theme music plays]
